For some reason the annotation capabilities of GameKnot would not let me annotate the remaining moves of the game - so here is what I would have said....Remember, White is already lost in this position with best play by Black.

18.Nf4 c4! 19.bxc4 (19.Bxc4 Nxc4 20.bxc4 Qb2+ 21.Kd1 Qxb1+ 22.Ke2 Qa2 would have held out longer perhaps, but is still losing.) 19...Bc3 (not so much to win the R as to keep with White K from escaping at d2). 20.Nxc2??? loses instantly (see below for alternatives) bxc3 21.Resigns since the next move is Qa1 mate.

I had expected 20.c5 Ne5 21.c6 Nbc4 22.Bxc4 Nxc4 23.Rd3 Qb2+ 24.Kd1 Nxe3+ 25.Rxe3 Qxb1+ 26.Ke2 Qxc2+ 27.Kf1 Qd1+ 28.Kf2 Qd2+ 29.Re2 Qxf4 when Black wins easily with his 2 extra bishops and Q-side passed pawns.
